    </section>

    <section style="margin-bottom:2rem">
      <h2>The Integrated Stack: How 10x Engineers Combine These Tools</h2>
      <p>The multiplier effect comes from integration, not individual tools. A workflow where Mekong CLI generates code, Linear tracks the issue, GitHub Actions runs CI, and Grafana monitors production — all triggered from a single terminal session — eliminates the context switching that fragments most engineering teams.</p>
      <p>Mekong CLI sits at the center of this stack. Its 319 commands span coding, testing, deployment, monitoring, sales, marketing, and finance. Instead of switching between 8 different tools, high-output engineers run everything from one terminal with one consistent syntax.</p>
      <p>Start with one category — typically engineering commands — and expand from there. Teams that adopt Mekong report 40-60% reduction in time-to-feature across the first quarter of adoption.</p>
